results.description: Paul Ramsey is tried for murdering his friend and can't reveal that an alien had taken over John Carter's body for fear of starting an invasion.

results.title: Masquerade
results.description: Tom is a practical, doubting kind of person, who has no time for flights of fancy. As a child, he never had time for fairy tales and nursery rhymes. Then a young girl invites him to a costume party. He goes to the wrong address and encounters real life fairy tale creatures

results.title: Midnight in the Wax Museum
results.description: Pierre La Roc is a criminal on the run, he climbs in through an open widow to escape the police, and finds himself in a wax museum. He hides as part of one of the exhibits as the police search the place. After the police leave, the wax figures come to life and chase La Roc out of the building, whereupon he then surrenders to the police. Later, a policeman discusses the strange case with a figure in a top hat, who later returns to his place as one of the wax figures in the museum.

results.title: I Am the Fantastic Dr. Droom!
results.description: In the City Medical Club, a group of doctors is discussing the Tibetan Lama who has requested medical attention from a Western physician.  Anthony Droom decides to lend a hand.  The Lama announced that he was fit to replace the aged master in his battle against evil.

results.title: This is Manoo! The Thing That Hid On Earth!
I Led the Strange Search for Manoo!
results.description: A college student aids an alien policeman hunt down an alien criminal hiding on earth, or is it the other way around?

results.title: The Comic
results.description: Stan Wepp is a TV comic with his own show. He hates that life. He misses the personal rapport with the audience, with doing his own material É and then somehow, magically, that's exactly what he ends updoing Æ and he couldnÕt be happier.

results.title: The World Below
results.description: Dr Droom defeats an attempt by Atlantis to conquer the surface world.

results.title: Rocky's Last Ride
results.description: Chisler Rocky gets a deal thats too good to be true, when a customer just "gives" him his car.

results.title: We Were Trapped in the Twilight World!
We Were Trapped in the Twilight World!
results.description: A young college student named Paul Harper hypothesizes that the past, present and future are occurring simultaneously in different dimensions; and if one could cross over into other dimensions, one could travel in time. Coincidently when Harper is later driving with his girlfriend, Cathy, they pass through a mist and enter a prehistoric world. They see a giant white bird, a saber-toothed tiger, some missing link-type near-humans (who Harper believes may be the progenitors of the Abominable Snowman); they then rescue a Neanderthal child from a giant sail-back lizard. After eluding a tyrannosaur, they are captured by a band of Neanderthals and offered up as sacrifice to a Pterodactyl hybrid. They are rescued by a man more advanced than the Neanderthals, who calls himself "Cro." He leads them back to the mist so they can go home. Of course the Dean doubts their story, until a necklace that Cro (now identified as a Cro-Magnon) had placed in their car is found.

results.title: The Masterpiece
results.description: Claude Duval is a portrait painter of high renown. Nobility is always asking for commissions from him. He now turns them all down, saying he wants to paint a landscape that shall be a symbol of man’s peace and contentment. He has the landlady lock him in. She is only allowed to open the door to bring him food. At the order of the queen, she is forced to unlock the door one day. The painter is gone, the portrait is finished – and a small figure reclining by a lake (in the painting) looks exactly like Claude Duval.

results.title: The Teddy Bear
results.description:
As a young girl, Carol had received a teddy bear that she kept by her side always. Her husband, Jim, is a surveyor, and is assigned to a rough rocky region for a short period. Jim spots some mountain lions tracks, and, gun in hand, goes off after the beast; however, the
mountain lion knocks Jim aside, damaging his gun, and heads for the tent where Carol is asleep. When Jim reaches the tent the mountain lion is dead and the teddy bear has some inexplicable scratches on it. Jim no longer criticizes Carol for wanting to take the bear everywhere.

results.title: Doctor Droom Meets Zemu!
results.description: Zemu appears to be a stage magician of incredible prowess. His name is on everyone's lips. Zemu announces he is running for governor. Dr. Droom not only discovers that Zemo is a fraud, but also is an alien from Saturn, bent on paving the way for an alien invasion. Of course, Dr. Droom overpowers him, hypnotizes him so that he'll reveal the truth, and turns him over to the authorities.

results.title: I Am Robot X
results.description: A fully functional robot with Artificial Intelligence is finally created, but a newspaperman raises the cry of its potential danger. Escaping a fearful mob, Robot X sets out to create more of his kind, so that their numbers will be too great to be menaced. An angry mob, unable to get into Robot X’s factory, chases the robot’s creator from his home. Meanwhile, Robot X, along with the robot army he’s created, marches through the city and capture the rabid newspaperman, exposing him as a member of a Martian fifth column, seeking to set up the subjugation of the earth. Knowing that humans are not ready to accept robots more intelligent than they, X than deactivates his entire army and himself as well. His creator muses that maybe, someday in the future, mankind may be ready for robots like X.

results.title: The Pact
results.description: Henry Conrad is a young writer who has been commissioned to write a book on the practice of witchcraft in the olden days. He cannot find any proof whether of not his own ancestor had made a deal with the Devil for the power of clairvoyance until one of the signers (the one with cloven hooves) of that Pact show up to explain to him the details.

results.title: Who or What Was ... the Bootblack?
results.description: Simon Sledge is a cruel and heartless businessman who delights in making others suffer. On the way to the biggest deal of his life, one that will eliminate the last of his competition, he stops for a shoeshine. Suddenly his feet are moving away from his destination, taking him far from the deal that will give him a monopoly in his field. He glances back at the bootblack who is revealed as an angel, and who says that when human laws can’t touch someone like Sledge, there are always higher laws.

results.title: What Lurks Within?
results.description: An alien spacecraft lands in a Midwestern farmer’s field. Dr. Droom is called to investigate. He tells everyone to stay out of sight, and orders a large derrick with a wrecking ball be brought to the site of the landing. Dr. Droom mans the derrick and slams the wrecking ball repeatedly into the side of the ship which, being built for interstellar travel, receives no physical damage. Dr. Droom then sends a telepathic message to the aliens saying that earthmen are peaceful, and asks the aliens to exit the ship so that they may be greeted in friendship. The aliens, who are not peaceful, blast away from earth – for, you see, Dr. Droom told them that he was the derrick knocking at their door.
